hokku-server (3.0.0~alpha1-12) unstable; urgency=low

  * Auto worker count: retune for thread-pool model. Old constants
    (250 MB reserve, 50 MB/worker) were calibrated for the process-pool
    where each worker forked the full interpreter. Threads share memory;
    measured incremental cost on Pi Zero 2 W is ~14 MB/worker under load.
    New constants: 100 MB OS reserve, 30 MB/worker. On a Pi with 200 MB
    free this resolves to 3 workers (matching the confirmed-safe manual
    setting) instead of the over-conservative 1.

