 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Sun, 10 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (3.0.0~alpha1-7) unstable; urgency=low

  * Pluggable face detection: AbstractFaceDetector + three concretes
    (yunet_opencv default, haar_opencv, yunet_onnx). New AppConfig field
    `face_detector` selects between them; config schema bumped v2→v3 with
    automatic migration. ImageClassifier observations carry which detector
    produced a cached has_face so swapping detectors triggers re-detection
    without invalidating the panel cache when results agree.
  * postinst pip-installs onnxruntime alongside opencv-headless so the
    yunet_onnx detector works out of the box.
  * Memory measurements for all three detectors recorded in
    docs/face_detection_memory_usage.md. Headline finding: yunet_opencv
    is actually the lightest both at startup AND during inference on the
    dev box; haar_opencv's detectMultiScale allocates ~110 MB transient
    pyramids and is the heaviest. The pluggable architecture stays
    valuable for future detectors but doesn't itself solve the Pi OOM —
    look elsewhere in the per-render budget.

