 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Sun, 10 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (3.0.0~alpha1-4) unstable; urgency=low

  * Split ImageManager into AbstractImageManager + SingleThreadedImageManager
    + MultiThreadedImageManager. ProcessPoolExecutor and the standalone
    RenderPool class are gone. Default image_worker_thread_count=1 now uses
    the inline single-threaded manager — no fork, no worker thread —
    restoring v2.x-class memory behaviour on the Pi Zero 2 W (the alpha1
    fork into a worker process duplicated opencv/PIL/numpy and OOM-killed
    the service on 512 MB hosts). Worker count >= 2 (or 0 = auto) uses a
    private ThreadPoolExecutor; single process, GIL-bound for now,
    parallelism for free once the dither hot path releases the GIL.
    _DbSaver removed (debounced async DB writes were a workaround for
    cross-process callback latency, not needed with threads).

