 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Wed, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (2.2.2-2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Lookup endpoints (DELETE / retry / original / thumbnail) no
    longer mutate the URL filename through werkzeug.secure_filename
    before look-up. secure_filename is right for upload (we want to
    rename unsafe characters before writing), wrong for lookup (we
    must match the on-disk name exactly — Samba- and SCP-uploaded
    files keep spaces, accents, parens, etc.). New _safe_lookup_name
    validator validates without mutating: rejects empty, '.', '..',
    null bytes, and any path separator. Fixes "Retry failed: Image
    not found" on filenames containing spaces or non-ASCII characters.
  * Web GUI: dither preset description moved into a (?) popover next
    to the preset selector (was a permanent inline span that bloated
    the row). Advanced dithering pipeline replaced the native
    <details> foldout with a [Custom...] button next to [Reset to
    preset]; the button toggles a hidden panel and label flips to
    [Hide advanced]; an x close button at panel top-right mirrors it.

 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Wed, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (2.2.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Pi-deployment fixes carried over from the parallel pi2w branch on
    top of the 2.2.x dither rewrite:
      - upload_dir/cache_dir defaults moved to /var/lib/hokku/upload
        and /var/lib/hokku/cache so DynamicUser StateDirectory writes
        work out of the box. Stale /images/* paths in older
        config.json files are migrated silently on load.
      - Timezone is no longer a stored config key. The server reads
        the host OS zone (set via timedatectl on the Pi). Removed
        from DEFAULT_CONFIG, _SAVE_KEYS, /api/config, /api/status,
        and the Configuration card in the web GUI; /api/time still
        returns the system zone for display.
      - Crash quarantine: a .processing marker is dropped before
        each conversion and removed on success. Orphans at startup
        are renamed to .failed. _list_images skips .failed entries
        so one bad image can't restart-loop the service after an
        OOM kill.
      - New failed-conversions UI: /hokku/api/status returns
        failed_files; /hokku/api/image/<name>/retry removes the
        marker and re-queues the image. The web UI renders an
        amber "Failed conversions" section with one-click Retry.
      - Web UI: server time moved to the top-right corner and
        trimmed to HH:MM:SS. Bulk upload is now sequential per-file
        instead of one giant multipart POST (fixes "Failed to
        fetch" on slow links). Non-images dropped via drag-drop
        are silently filtered.
      - _ensure_thumbnail uses Image.draft() to keep RAM bounded
        when generating a 300x300 thumbnail from a 12 MP source.

