  * Dither pipeline memory footprint cut from ~490 MB to ~68 MB peak at
    production canvas (1200x1600). Changes:
      - Early JPEG draft downsample so a 32 MP source no longer sits in
        RAM as 96 MB of RGB through the DRC peak.
      - Lab-space helpers kept in float32 end-to-end (halves every
        intermediate) with dtype preservation via typed constants.
      - `np.where(cond, toe, shoulder)` on full-canvas buffers replaced
        with in-place masked updates — saves a second canvas-sized
        allocation per branch.
      - `_xyz_to_lab` and `_lab_to_srgb_f32` reuse the Lab buffer via
        in-place matmul and channel-slot reshuffling instead of
        `np.stack([L, a, b])`.
      - Fused adaptive saturation + DRC into a single Lab round-trip.
      - Source image freed before Lab transforms allocate.
    Same output bits; lower peak allocation on the Pi.
  * New webserver/tests/test_dither_memory.py: 18-combo (6 images x 3
    presets) half-canvas matrix at 30 MB ceiling (proxies 100 MB at
    full canvas) plus opt-in @pytest.mark.memory full-canvas smoke
    tests verifying < 100 MB on the real production path.
  * (Pi-deployment fixes from the parallel pi2w branch — paths,
    timezone removal, crash quarantine, failed-images UI, sequential
    upload — folded into 2.2.2-1 below as a follow-up commit.)

 -- Dennis Fleurbaaij <mail@dennisfleurbaaij.com>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hokku-server (2.2.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Dither pipeline exposed as editable presets + full per-stage
    Advanced panel in the web UI: every knob (autocontrast, gamma,
    brightness/contrast/sharpness, saturation mode+thresholds,
    dynamic-range compression chroma mode+thresholds, palette LUT
    mode+hue-cutoff+neutral-chroma, B&W fallback, dither kernel)
    is toggleable/tunable with a per-knob (?) help popover. Three
    named presets: Floyd–Steinberg (pre-2.0), Atkinson soft, and
    Atkinson hue-aware (default).
  * Settings form loaded ONCE via new /api/config; /api/status poll
    no longer returns config so user edits can't be clobbered mid-
    typing. New /api/dither/preview renders an unsaved config at
    half resolution for interactive feedback.
  * Config schema change: nested "dither" object replaces the flat
    dither_algorithm string. Legacy string is silently dropped on
    load. Cache key now hashes the normalised dither config so any
    knob change invalidates just its own renders (_CACHE_VERSION
    bumped to v3; existing caches are discarded on upgrade).
  * Hue-aware LUTs memoised by (hue_cutoff_deg, neutral_chroma) so
    tweaking the knob doesn't pay a 32³ rebuild per render.
  * docs/dithering.md updated to match the preset/knob schema.
  * Tests: 294 passing, including a new 162-case permutation matrix
    (24 dither configs × 6 real-world test images) with hard
    invariants + soft artifact bounds (neutral-leak ≤ 35%, B&W
    fallback ≥ 95% monochrome).

